                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@IwillnotexistIdonotexist: Clobbering r8-r11 is the least important reason!  #1 is: only supports 32-bit args / return values.  #2 is: strace decodes it wrong, so it&apos;s hard to debug.  #3 is: low performance.  #4 is: register args don&apos;t match x86-64 function-calling, and it uses &lt;code&gt;ebx&lt;/code&gt; which is call-preserved.  (Rankings vary by use-case / beginner or not, but I think those all outweigh clearing r8-r11 all the time.)  Anyway, I&apos;ll think about a better intro.&lt;/span&gt;

