                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@ojdo: I have Python 3.9.5 on Kubuntu 21.04.The folder I want to &apos;be public&apos;, so to speak, contains a &lt;b&gt;filebox.py&lt;/b&gt; file.   I followed your instructions, got site.USERSITE path, created &lt;b&gt;customizesite.py&lt;/b&gt; there, added the folder as you wrote.Launched customize.py. The folder is in sys.path.**&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;import filebox** : no errors. Closed python prompt and launched it again.The folder is no more in sys.path. In the console, if folder path is the working directory &lt;b&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; import filebox&lt;/b&gt; works. Otherwise I got a ModuleNotFoundError: No module named &apos;filebox&apos;.&lt;/span&gt;

